nd future research. It will be of interest to scholars and undergraduate and postgraduate students in the fields of English literature, modernism, women's writing, and gender and sexuality studies, and to general readers.  aMode of access: Internet via World Wide Web.  aIn English.0 aDescription based on online resource; title from PDF title page (publisher's Web site, viewed 06. Mrz 2024) 0aEnglish fictionx20th century. 0aEnglish fictiony20th century. 4aLiterature Studies 2020. 7aLITERARY CRITICISM / European / English, Irish, Scottish, Welsh.2bisacsh  aGender.  aLesbian.  aLiterature.  aModernism.  aRadclyffe Hall.  aReligion.  aSexuality.  aSupernatural.  aWomen Writers.  aWorld War I.1 aFunke, Jana, econtributor.4ctb4https://id.loc.gov/vocabulary/relators/ctb1 aFunke, Jana, eeditor.4edt4http://id.loc.gov/vocabulary/relators/edt08iTitle is part of eBook package:dDe GruytertManchester University Press 2016 eBook-Packagez978311128282440uhttps://doi.org/10.7765/978178499766340uhttps://www.degruyter.com/isbn/9781784997663423Coveruhttps://www.degruyter.com/document/cover/isbn/9781784997663/original  a978-3-11-128282-4  Manchester University Press 2016 eBook-Packageb2016  aGBV-deGruyter-alles